.TH "__phy_modify" 9 "__phy_modify" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__phy_modify \- Convenience function for modifying a PHY register
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __phy_modify
.BI "(struct phy_device *phydev "  ","
.BI "u32 regnum "  ","
.BI "u16 mask "  ","
.BI "u16 set "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phydev" 12
the phy_device struct
.IP "regnum" 12
register number to modify
.IP "mask" 12
bit mask of bits to clear
.IP "set" 12
new value of bits set in mask to write to \fIregnum\fP
.SH "NOTE"
MUST NOT be called from interrupt context,
because the bus read/write functions may wait for an interrupt
to conclude the operation.
